This Rust code implements an email scheduling system using a `VecDeque` data structure. It allows users to add emails with IDs and timestamps, prioritizes urgent emails by shuffling the queue occasionally, and logs each processed email with its timestamp. The system has a limitation on the size of the queue to avoid overloading and only allows pushing new emails to the back and popping the oldest emails from the front for processing.

